This paper is about natural language processing for biomedical and clinical text, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of statistical models, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of code and tools, which could fall under the category of computer systems and networking (cs.CY). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of models on different datasets, which could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR).
